#: ../../../api/abc.rst:44
msgid ""
"This method will be used by `~psycopg.sql.Literal` to convert a value client-"
"side."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/abc.rst:47
msgid ""
"This method only makes sense for text dumpers; the result of calling it on a "
"binary dumper is undefined. It might scratch your car, or burn your cake. "
"Don't tell me I didn't warn you."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/sphinx/ext/autodoc/_sentinels.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.abc.Dumper.oid:1
msgid "The oid to pass to the server, if known; 0 otherwise (class attribute)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/abc.rst:53
msgid ""
"If the OID is not specified, PostgreSQL will try to infer the type from the "
"context, but this may fail in some contexts and may require a cast (e.g. "
"specifying :samp:`%s::{type}` for its placeholder)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../api/abc.rst:57
msgid ""
"You can use the `psycopg.adapters`\\ ``.`` `~psycopg.adapt.AdaptersMap."
"types` registry to find the OID of builtin types, and you can use `~psycopg."
"types.TypeInfo` to extend the registry to custom types."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/abc.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.abc.Dumper.get_key:1
