#: of psycopg.abc.Dumper.get_key:3 psycopg.abc.Dumper.upgrade:3
msgid "The object to convert"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/abc.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.abc.Dumper.get_key:4 psycopg.abc.Dumper.upgrade:4
msgid "The format to convert to"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/abc.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.abc.Dumper.get_key:6
msgid ""
"Normally the type of the object is all it takes to define how to dump the "
"object to the database. For instance, a Python `~datetime.date` can be "
"simply converted into a PostgreSQL :sql:`date`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/abc.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.abc.Dumper.get_key:10
msgid "In a few cases, just the type is not enough. For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/abc.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.abc.Dumper.get_key:12
msgid ""
"A Python `~datetime.datetime` could be represented as a :sql:`timestamptz` "
"or a :sql:`timestamp`, according to whether it specifies a `!tzinfo` or not."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/abc.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.abc.Dumper.get_key:16
msgid ""
"A Python int could be stored as several Postgres types: int2, int4, int8, "
"numeric. If a type too small is used, it may result in an overflow. If a "
"type too large is used, PostgreSQL may not want to cast it to a smaller type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/abc.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.abc.Dumper.get_key:21
msgid ""
"Python lists should be dumped according to the type they contain to convert "
"them to e.g. array of strings, array of ints (and which size of int?...)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/abc.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.abc.Dumper.get_key:25
msgid ""
"In these cases, a dumper can implement `!get_key()` and return a new class, "
"or sequence of classes, that can be used to identify the same dumper again. "
"If the mechanism is not needed, the method should return the same `!cls` "
"object passed in the constructor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/abc.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.abc.Dumper.get_key:30
msgid ""
"If a dumper implements `get_key()` it should also implement `upgrade()`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/abc.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.abc.Dumper.upgrade:1
msgid "Return a new dumper to manage `!obj`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/abc.py:docstring
#: of psycopg.abc.Dumper.upgrade:6
msgid ""
"Once `Transformer.get_dumper()` has been notified by `get_key()` that this "
"Dumper class cannot handle `!obj` itself, it will invoke `!upgrade()`, which "
"should return a new `Dumper` instance, which will be reused for every "
"objects for which `!get_key()` returns the same result."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.14/site-packages/psycopg/abc.py:docstring
